00:00:03.460 --> 00:00:07.440
In a previous video we've already show you
how to replace or repair an inner tube

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:10.660
when you're out training if you puncture,
but what if you're out training you've got

00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:14.040
a pump with you but you've run out of
inner tubes, and you've got no patches?

00:00:14.040 --> 00:00:17.720
Well, there are a couple of methods that
you can use to try and get you home.

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:22.550
Hi, there. Yeah, can you come and
pick me up, please? First thing's first,

00:00:22.550 --> 00:00:25.990
find yourself a safe place, away from
the road and away from the traffic.

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:28.382
Then of course, you're going to
need to take the wheel out.

00:00:28.382 --> 00:00:31.300
♪ [music] ♪

00:00:33.984 --> 00:00:38.347
Just like any other time that you change a
punctured one, I'm going to check inside

00:00:38.347 --> 00:00:43.668
the tire, as we did in the other
video, just do it gently just in case.

00:00:43.668 --> 00:00:46.600
♪ [music] ♪

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:52.494
Next thing, we've got to find out
where the hole is on this inner tube.

00:00:52.494 --> 00:00:55.400
♪ [music] ♪

00:00:59.824 --> 00:01:03.341
Make sure you keep your finger
exactly where it is if you don't

00:01:03.341 --> 00:01:06.905
want to lose the exact point
that the whole is. All we're

00:01:06.905 --> 00:01:15.120
going to do is cut a knot in the tire,
so the hole is just up here, to try and

00:01:15.120 --> 00:01:20.640
isolate the hole and stop any air getting
to that particular part. That looks

00:01:20.640 --> 00:01:26.000
a bit crude. You want to get that knot as
close to the end of the tube as possible,

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:29.296
because, of course, you're shortening it
but there is quite a lot of stretchiness

00:01:29.296 --> 00:01:36.635
in these inner tubes, so it should still
fill the entire tire. Just a simple knot

00:01:36.635 --> 00:01:44.186
will do, just trying to get this one up
right towards the end. Now, if it looks

00:01:44.186 --> 00:01:49.716
crude, that's because it is, but the idea
is that this bodge will hopefully get us

00:01:49.716 --> 00:01:51.340
back home. Let's give it a go.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:54.300
♪ [music] ♪

00:01:54.566 --> 00:01:58.877
As you can see, that seems to work okay.
There's no actual air in that end part

00:01:58.877 --> 00:02:02.267
where the hole is, and it's
staying up. All good so far.

00:02:02.267 --> 00:02:05.200
♪ [music] ♪

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:19.290
Here we go, it's on. Now we don't want
to put it up to 100 PSI like we might do

00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:23.660
ordinarily, because that's a weak point
now. This is simply a bodge job to get you

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:26.960
home so don't carry on with 100 mile
ride either, you just want to take the

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:32.128
most direct route back to your home or
wherever you're staying. Well, what do

00:02:32.128 --> 00:02:35.652
you do if the single knot bodge doesn't
work? Well, it should do if it's just a

00:02:35.652 --> 00:02:39.282
small hole, but if you find that you've
got a rip and, of course, you go into

00:02:39.282 --> 00:02:46.188
GCN's bodge number two. So, I think I've
managed to isolate where the hole is in

00:02:46.188 --> 00:02:51.132
my tube. As you can see, this is a big
gash, so that single knot might not work,

00:02:51.132 --> 00:02:54.835
as it's more difficult to isolate this
hole and stop the air coming out. So, what

00:02:54.835 --> 00:02:58.451
do you do in this situation? Well, we're
going to make two knots, but first of all,

00:02:58.451 --> 00:03:07.050
we need to rip the inner tube into two
parts. The aim is to rip the inner tube

00:03:07.050 --> 00:03:17.010
and not to rip your hands. There we
go. Now what are we going to do?

00:03:17.010 --> 00:03:22.770
So, now we're ready to make the two knots.
So, starting at one end of the inner tube,

00:03:22.770 --> 00:03:28.350
let's put a simple knot in it. Now, you
want the knot to be fairly close to the

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:34.200
end but of course, not too close so
there's less chance of the air coming

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:39.060
through. Once you've got it roughly like
that, around about an inch to spare at the

00:03:39.060 --> 00:03:44.630
end, just pull it as
tight as you can get it.

00:03:44.630 --> 00:03:47.600
♪ [music] ♪

00:04:13.803 --> 00:04:17.585
But what do you do if the single knot
doesn't work, and the double knot doesn't

00:04:17.585 --> 00:04:23.544
work? Well you go on to GCN bodge number
three which is grass. Now, I always take

00:04:23.544 --> 00:04:27.800
some out with me in my back pocket,
and we're going to stuff that in the tire.

00:04:27.800 --> 00:04:30.800
♪ [music] ♪

